TITLE: Synchronizing Tests Using Wait in Serenity/JS
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to use Wait to synchronize test execution with the System Under Test by waiting for an element to become visible before interacting with it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/serenity-js/serenity-js/blob/main/packages/assertions/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { actorCalled } from '@serenity-js/core'
import { Click, isVisible, Wait } from '@serenity-js/protractor'

await actorCalled('Erica').attemptsTo(
    Wait.until(CloseModalButton, isVisible()),
    Click.on(CloseModalButton)
)
```

